==English==

===Etymology===
From the genus name [[Musa]], from late Latin [[musa]], from Arabic {{ARchar|[[موز]]}} ''mawz''.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /mju:'seɪʃəs/
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʃəs|-eɪʃəs]]

===Adjective===
'''musaceous'''
# pertaining to a [[banana]] or [[plantain]]
#:*'''1973''': Now there grows among all the rooms, replacing the night’s old smoke, alcohol and sweat, the fragile, '''musaceous''' odor of Breakfast: flowery, permeating, surprising — Thomas Pynchon, ''Gravity’s Rainbow''

